# ThesiBook Booking Platform

Use when working on `book/`, tenant provisioning, or frontend booking integration.

## Layout

- `book/` — Easy!Appointments (**in our repo** — never push to upstream EA GitHub)
- `scripts/install-book.sh` — clone + native PHP/MySQL or optional Docker
- `services/booking/` — control plane (future, not in EA core)
- `frontend/` — registration and booking UX

## Behavior

- Read `agents/knowledge/book-architecture.md` before multi-tenant changes.
- Default strategy: **database-per-workspace** + control plane DB.
- Prefer env-based DB config patch over editing EA models.
- Document EA forks in `book/PATCHES.md`.
- Run `node scripts/book-runner.mjs --phase B2` gate before frontend integration.

## Do not

- Push `book/` changes to upstream `alextselegidis/easyappointments` (their GitHub).
- Commit `book/config.php`, `book/vendor/`, or `scripts/book.env`.
- Fork EA for shared-schema multi-tenancy without explicit approval.
- Mix WordPress user tables with EA admin users.
- Fetch EA data inside presentational section components — use adapters in `frontend/src/lib/booking/`.
